data.name: Braised Carp with Onions and Carrots
data.quickTastyDescription: A comforting dish of tender carp braised with sweet onions and carrots, perfect for a cozy dinner.
detailedCookingInstructions: Heat vegetable oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
Slice the onion and carrot; add them to the skillet and saut√© until softened, about 5-7 minutes.
Add the carp fillets to the skillet, gently nestling them among the vegetables.
Pour in the water, add salt, pepper, and bay leaf.
Cover and let it simmer for about 20 minutes, or until the fish is cooked through and flakes easily with a fork.
